A second admonition to the parliament Cartwright, Thomas, 1535-1603, attributed name.
[76] p.
J. Stroud?, [Hemel Hempstead? : 1572]
Dubiously attributed to Thomas Cartwright. Caption title; imprint suggested by STC. Colophon (leaf H5) reads: Imprinted we know where, and whan, Iudge you the place and you can. Caption title (leaf H5) reads: Certaine articles, collected and taken (as it is thought) by the byshops out of a little boke entituled an Admonition to the Parliament, with an answere to the same. Containing a confirmation of the sayde booke in those notes. Signatures: *⁴ A-G⁴ H⁶ (H6 blank). Reproduction of the original in the Cambridge University Library.
